The statistics available show that substantially the greater proportion of calls are made successfully the first time but the fact remains that perhaps in one's individual experience one always feels that one is on the side of those who do not succeed in achieving that. Section 9(2) of the Act states clearly that in providing this service the Post Office shall have regard
…to the desirability of improving and developing its operating systems;
and it is engaged in doing just that.
